168‚Üí                /* Anki-Android adds mathjax-needs-to-render" as a class to the card when
169‚Üí                   it detects both \( and \) or \[ and \].
170‚Üí
171‚Üí                   This does not control *loading* MathJax, but rather controls whether or not MathJax
172‚Üí                   renders content.  We hide all the content until MathJax renders, because otherwise
173‚Üí                   the content loads, and has to reflow after MathJax renders, and it's unsightly.
174‚Üí                   However, if we hide all the content every time, folks don't like the repainting after
175‚Üí                   every question or answer.  This is a middle-ground, where there is no repainting due to
176‚Üí                   MathJax on non-MathJax cards, and on MathJax cards, there is a small flicker, but there's
